##To deploy your code into a function app in azure:
first download: "azure cli" and "azure function app"

In command propmt:
1. Log in to Azure :
az login

2. Create the Function App :
az functionapp create \
  --resource-group <RESOURCEGROUP> \
  --consumption-plan-location eastus2 \
  --runtime python \
  --runtime-version 3.10 \
  --functions-version 4 \
  --name my-chatbot-func \
  --storage-account <STORAGEACCOUNT> \
  --os-type Linux
 
3.Publish Function Code to Azure:    
func azure functionapp publish my-chatbot-func --python      #This command uploads your local code to the Function App

4.List Deployed Functions and Endpoints:
az functionapp function list \
  --name my-chatbot-func \
  --resource-group <RESOURCEGROUP>\
  --query "[].invokeUrlTemplate" -o tsv       #This shows the full HTTP trigger URLs for your deployed functions.

5.Example Endpoint Test:
https://<FUNCTION_APP_NAME>.azurewebsites.net/api/<FUNCTION_NAME>?message=Hello






